==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carrol
<hw>Car"rol</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OF. <ets>carole</ets> a sort of circular space, or carol.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A small closet or inclosure built against a
window on the inner side, to sit in for study. The word was used as late
as the 16th century. The term <er>carrel</er>, of the same has largely
superseded its use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>A bay window may thus be called a <qex>carol</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Parker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carolin</ent>⟦br⟧

